SIMPLE: watery
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Watery
<hw>Wa"ter*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>waeterig</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to water; consisting of
water.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>watery</xex> god.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Dryden.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧Fish within their <xex>watery</xex> residence.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Milton.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Abounding with water; wet; hence, tearful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Resembling water; thin or transparent, as a liquid;
<as>as, <ex>watery</ex> humors</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The oily and <qex>watery</qex> parts of the aliment.</q>
<rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Hence, abounding in thin, tasteless, or insipid
fluid; tasteless; insipid; vapid; spiritless.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Watt</ent>⟦br⟧
